{{otheruses|Broad interpretation of the extended area of Munakata and Munakata [[Shingun]]|Other uses}}
== Munakata (宗像) ==
'''Munakata''' (宗像) refers to the area encompassing {{ill|Munakata City|ja|宗像市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Munakata District|ja|宗像郡|12=draft|12=draft}}, and their surrounding regions.
The exact extent of the surrounding areas is not clearly defined, but during the {{ill|Asuka period|ja|飛鳥時代|12=draft|12=draft}}, the historical Munakata District included the northwestern part of {{ill|Kurate District|ja|鞍手郡|12=draft|12=draft}} (western {{ill|Miyawaka|ja|宮若市|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Kurate|ja|鞍手町|12=draft|12=draft}}), which formed the ancient broad Munakata region.
The extent of ancient Munakata covered Munakata City and District, the northwestern part of Kurate District (the western area of Miyawaka and Kurate Town), part of the former {{ill|Onga District|ja|遠賀郡|12=draft|12=draft}}, and the eastern part of {{ill|Kasuyagun|ja|糟屋郡|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Koga|ja|古賀市|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Shingū|ja|新宮町|12=draft|12=draft}}).
During the {{ill|Sengoku period (Japan)|ja|戦国時代|12=draft|12=draft}}, Munakata referred to what is now Munakata City, Fukutsu City, the area east of the {{ill|Onga River|ja|遠賀川|12=draft|12=draft}} in Onga District, the northwestern part of Kurate District, and the {{ill|Shingū Coast|ja|新宮海岸|12=draft|12=draft}}, which includes the Koga Beach area. Since the eastern part of Onga District was under the control of the local warlord {{ill|Asō clan|ja|麻生氏|12=draft|12=draft}}, who submitted to the {{ill|Munakata clan|ja|宗像氏|1=Munakata clan|fr|Clan Munakata|12=draft|12=draft}} after their conflict, it was sometimes included in the Munakata domain as well.
However, historically, the term Munakata often referred to the lands controlled by the Munakata clan. The territories that consistently remained under Munakata clan rule included Munakata City, most of Fukutsu City except for the Saigo region, former {{ill|Wakamiya Town|ja|若宮町|12=draft|12=draft}}, the northern part of former {{ill|Miyata Town|ja|宮田町|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Okagaki|ja|岡垣町|12=draft|12=draft}}, and a small part of {{ill|Ongatown|ja|遠賀町|12=draft|12=draft}}.
This region has long had deep connections with {{ill|China|ja|中国大陸|12=draft|12=draft}} and the {{ill|Korean Peninsula|ja|朝鮮半島|12=draft|12=draft}}, and it is well known for its active engagement in {{ill|trade|ja|貿易|12=draft|12=draft}} since ancient times.
